  <md:abstract><para>By the end of this section, you will be able to:</para> 
<list>
<item>Describe the electric field within a conductor at equilibrium</item>
<item>Describe the electric field immediately outside the surface of a charged conductor at equilibrium</item>
<item>Explain why if the field is not as described in the first two objectives, the conductor is not at equilibrium</item></list></md:abstract>
  <md:language>en</md:language>
